e%20at%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20we%20might%20go%20out%20to%20a%20bar%2C%20where%20it'll%20cost%20between%20%C2%A310%20to%20%C2%A320%20to%20get%20a%20couple%20of%20shots%20and%20a%20couple%20of%20beers%20or%20glasses%20of%20wine.%20But%20when%20we're%20going%3Cem%3E%20out%3C%2Fem%3E%20out%2C%20we'll%20go%20to%20a%20club.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClubs%20are%20between%20%C2%A35%20and%20%C2%A315%20entry.%20But%20on%20Wednesdays%20we%20can%20get%20into%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pologlasgow.co.uk%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EPolo%20Lounge%2C%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20popular%20local%20club%2C%20for%20free%20with%20a%20student%20ID.%20Drinks%20there%20cost%20another%20%C2%A315%20to%20%C2%A330.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20go%20out%20two%20or%20three%20times%20a%20month.%20But%20I'll%20do%20something%20more%20casual%2C%20like%20grab%20a%20pint%20with%20friends%2C%20around%20five%20times%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMini%20golf%20and%20laser%20tag%20are%20also%20popular%20activities%20for%20local%20students.%20Those%20add%20another%20%C2%A320%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat's%20the%20biggest%20cost%20difference%20you've%20noticed%20between%20Germany%2C%20Scotland%2C%20and%20the%20US%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20noticed%20the%20biggest%20difference%20in%20groceries.%20In%20Germany%2C%20we%20have%20different%20types%20of%20grocery%20stores%2C%20but%20they%20are%20pretty%20similar%20in%20price%20and%20they%20all%20sell%20good%20quality%20food.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20moved%20to%20the%20UK%2C%20I%20noticed%20there%20are%20different%20tiers%20of%20stores.%20For%20example%2C%20you%20have%20Tesco%2C%20Sainsbury's%2C%20Asda%2C%20which%20are%20more%20about%20the%20price%20than%20food%20quality.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20I%20see%20that%20in%20ads%2C%20it's%20always%20about%20price%20matching%20and%20being%20the%20cheapest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20noticed%20the%20same%20thing%20in%20the%20US.%20Higher%20quality%20stores%2C%20like%20Whole%20Foods%20or%20Ralphs%2C%20definitely%20charge%20a%20premium.%20Whereas%20in%20Germany%20it's%20pretty%20standard%20no%20matter%20where%20you%20shop.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20major%20difference%20living%20in%20the%20UK%20is%20the%20cost%20of%20alcohol.%20There%20is%20a%20very%20high%20alcohol%20tax%2C%20which%20makes%20drinks%20very%20expensive.%20In%20Scotland%20I%20would%20pay%20between%20%C2%A330%20and%20%C2%A350%20for%20a%20bottle%20of%20gin.%20But%20in%20Germany%20I'd%20pay%20between%20%C2%A35%20and%20%C2%A320.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20do%20you%20think%20is%20the%20biggest%20difference%20between%20you%20and%20American%2021-year-olds%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20many%20Americans%2C%20I%20have%20no%20student%20debt.%20That's%20why%20I%20think%20Europe%20is%20such%20a%20great%20place%20to%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20tuition%20is%20free%20because%20I%20started%20school%20before%202020%2C%20when%20the%20UK%20was%20still%20part%20of%20the%20European%20Union%2C%20so%20EU%20citizens%20could%20go%20for%20free.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithout%20that%20debt%2C%20I%20feel%20like%20I%20get%20to%20start%20life%20fresh%20after%20graduating.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20did%20you%20learn%20about%20finances%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20learned%20a%20lot%20about%20investing%20from%20my%20parents%2C%20especially%20my%20mom%20because%20she's%20really%20good%20at%20that%20stuff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhatever%20I%20have%20left%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20month%2C%20I%20transfer%20into%20my%20vanguard%20portfolio.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20invest%20in%20S%20%26amp%3B%20P%20500%20because%20it's%20quite%20easy%20to%20just%20set%20that%20aside%20and%20know%20at%20some%20point%20it%20might%20grow%20and%20I%20will%20be%20able%20to%20use%20it%20as%20security.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20our%20generation%20loves%20to%20dream%20big%20and%20wants%20to%20be%20rich.%20But%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20don't%20really%20know%20how%20to%20do%20it.%20I%20feel%20like%20stocks%20are%20a%20way%20to%20invest%20in%20something%20bigger%2C%20something%20quite%20important.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feuropean-gen-z-no-student-debt-spends-money-each-month-2023-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690378449000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64c03f31d1a36600194c7b1b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feuropean-gen-z-no-student-debt-spends-money-each-month-2023-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Joshua%20is%20a%20European%20Gen%20Zer%20who%20moved%20to%20Scotland%20for%20tuition-free%20college.%20He%20now%20lives%20off%20%24900%20a%20month%2C%20with%20some%20help%20from%20his%20parents.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ayork%40insider.com%20(Alexandra%20York)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feuropean-gen-z-no-student-debt-spends-money-each-month-2023-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Chien-Shiung%20Wu%2C%20a%20nuclear%20physicist%20who%20worked%20on%20the%20Manhattan%20Project%2C%20spent%20her%20career%20fighting%20for%20gender%20equality%20in%20science%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222414%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Chien-Shiung%20Wu%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64c00c9ced4f460019635e2e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221810%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EChien-Shiung%20Wu%20in%20a%20laboratory%20at%20Columbia%20University%20in%201958.%3Cp%3EBettmann%2FContributor%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EChien-Shiung%20Wu%20was%20a%20Chinese%20physicist%20who%20was%20instrumental%20to%20the%20Manhattan%20Project.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EWu%20was%20awarded%20the%20prestigious%20Wolf%20Prize%20for%20Physics%20after%20being%20denied%20a%20Nobel%20Prize%20that%20her%20male%20colleagues%20received.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EWu%20also%20advocated%20for%20gender%20equality%2C%20refusing%20to%20adopt%20her%20husband's%20last%20name%20and%20demanding%20equal%20pay.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EChristopher%20Nolan's%20blockbuster%20film%20%26quot%3BOppenheimer%26quot%3B%20largely%20omits%20the%20women%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmanhattan-project-oppenheimer-black-scientists-history-atomic-bomb-science-2023-7%5C%22%3Epeople%20of%20color%20who%20worked%20on%20the%20real-life%20Manhattan%20Project%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20instead%20zeroing%20in%20on%20the%20white%20men%20involved%20in%20the%20US%20government's%20atomic%20bomb%20initiative.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChien-Shiung%20Wu%20is%20a%20physicist%20who%20broke%20through%20both%20gender%20and%20racial%20barriers%20in%201940s%20America%2C%20wowing%20the%20science%20community%20with%20her%20significant%20contributions%20to%20the%20Manhattan%20Project.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWu%20was%20born%20in%20Jiangsu%20province%2C%20China%2C%20on%20May%2031%2C%201912%2C%20to%20a%20family%20of%20intellectual%20revolutionaries.%20Wu's%20mother%20was%20a%20teacher%20who%20valued%20education%20for%20both%20genders%2C%20while%20her%20father%20was%20an%20engineer%20who%20also%20advocated%20for%20women's%20equality.%20He%20became%20an%20activist%20during%20the%201911%20Revolution%2C%20which%20ended%20imperial%20rule%20and%20established%20the%20more%20modernized%20Republic%20of%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWu%20was%20especially%20close%20with%20her%20father%2C%20who%20encouraged%20her%20interests%20and%20surrounded%20her%20with%20books%2C%20magazines%2C%20and%20newspapers.%20Instead%20of%20children's%20stories%2C%20Wu%20would%20listen%20to%20her%20father%20read%20from%20scientific%20journals%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Fbooks%2Fedition%2FMadame_Wu_Chien_Shiung%2FC0PLygAACAAJ%3Fhl%3Den%5C%22%20t