20the%20disabled%20population%20in%20the%20country.%20Numerous%20studies%20have%20revealed%20that%20households%20with%20disabled%20members%20face%20higher%20levels%20of%20multidimensional%20poverty%20compared%20to%20those%20without%20disabilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdmittedly%2C%20defining%20disability%20is%20as%20challenging%20as%20defining%20poverty%2C%20but%20their%20inclusion%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20necessarily%20have%20to%20be.%20People%20with%20disabilities%20are%20believed%20to%20be%20at%20a%20heightened%20risk%20of%20poverty.%20Sadly%2C%20the%20way%20poverty%20is%20measured%20often%20overlooks%20their%20unique%20challenges%20and%20needs%2C%20leaving%20them%20invisible%20in%20poverty%20indices.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20national%20Mutlidimensional%20Poverty%20Index%20(MPI)%20comprises%20three%20equally%20weighted%20dimensions%3A%20health%2C%20education%2C%20and%20standard%20of%20living%2C%20which%20are%20represented%20by%20a%20total%20of%2012%20indicators.%20While%20using%20a%20multidimensional%20index%20to%20discuss%20poverty%20in%20India%20is%20a%20novel%20approach%2C%20the%20report%E2%80%99s%20limited%20health%20indicators%2C%20such%20as%20nutrition%2C%20child%20and%20adolescent%20mortality%2C%20and%20maternal%20health%2C%20fall%20short%20in%20considering%20the%20impact%20of%20disability%20on%20poverty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20family%20with%20a%20disabled%20person%20%E2%80%93%20irrespective%20of%20whether%20the%20disability%20is%20by%20birth%20or%20acquired%20later%20%E2%80%93%20faces%20recurring%20medical%20expenditure%20throughout%20their%20lifetime%2C%20influencing%20all%2012%20indicators%20in%20various%20ways.%20However%2C%20the%20term%20disability%20has%20been%20used%20only%20in%20a%20preventive%20context%20relating%20to%20maternal%20health%20and%20disabilities%20occurring%20at%20birth%20in%20the%20entire%20report.%20The%20omission%20of%20disabilities%20as%20a%20factor%20in%20health%20in%20families%20that%20have%20a%20disabled%20member%20neglects%20the%20long-term%2C%20recurring%20effect%20of%20health%20costs%2C%20impacting%20all%20the%20other%20indicators%20in%20the%20MPI.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20in%20the%20education%20dimension%2C%20a%20person%20with%20a%20locomotor%20disability%20might%20have%20low%20or%20no%20school%20attendance%20due%20to%20the%20lack%20of%20accessible%20schools.%20This%20impacts%20the%20%E2%80%98school%20attendance%E2%80%99%20indicator.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20a%20child%20with%20autism%20may%20attend%20school%20every%20day%20and%20not%20be%20categorised%20as%20%E2%80%98deprived%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20%E2%80%98years%20of%20schooling%E2%80%99%20indicator%2C%20but%20this%20does%20not%20necessarily%20mean%20that%20the%20child%20has%20successfully%20achieved%20the%20required%20level%20of%20education.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fmultidimensional-poverty-best-states-niti-aayogs-report-performance%5C%22%3EMultidimensional%20Poverty%3A%20How%20Do%20the%20Best%20States%20in%20Niti%20Aayog%E2%80%99s%20Report%20Perform%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDisability%E2%80%99s%20impact%20on%20poverty%20can%20thus%20remain%20invisible%20in%20such%20cases.%20Including%20an%20indicator%20of%20sustainable%20livelihood%20would%20highlight%20the%20challenges%20faced%20by%20the%20disabled%20community%2C%20considering%20that%20accessibility%20and%20discrimination%20are%20most%20apparent%20in%20the%20livelihood%20sphere.%20Such%20cases%2C%20where%20the%20longitudinal%20impact%20on%20poverty%20is%20disguised%2C%20necessitate%20better-structured%20indicators.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20challenges%20of%20using%20a%20monetary%20approach%20to%20poverty%20from%20a%20disability%20perspective%20are%20the%20assumption%20that%20households%20share%20resources%20equitably%2C%20that%20the%20consumption%20needs%20of%20all%20members%20are%20the%20same%2C%20and%20that%20the%20resources%20available%20to%20the%20members%20are%20accessible%20to%20a%20person%20with%20a%20disability.%20A%20social%20exclusion%20or%20relative%20poverty%20measure%20seeks%20to%20understand%20poverty%20from%20a%20relative%20standpoint%3B%20though%20this%20seems%20apt%2C%20it%20would%20invariably%20underestimate%20poverty%20among%20the%20disabled%20population.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20a%20disability%20standpoint%2C%20it%20helps%20to%20understand%20poverty%20from%20a%20capability%20perspective.%20Measurement%20of%20poverty%20using%20the%20capability%20approach%20focuses%20on%20deprivations%20in%20certain%20basic%20capabilities.%20Using%20the%20capabilities%20approach%20in%20a%20multidimensional%20poverty%20index%20would%20inevitably%20include%20people%20with%20disabilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20MPI%20and%20the%20capabilities%20approach%20both%20have%20their%20own%20demerits%2C%20it%20seems%20an%20amalgamation%20of%20both%20methods%20would%20give%20the%20needed%20intersectional%20data%20for%20apt%20policymaking.%20One%20of%20the%20criticisms%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fophi.org.uk%2Fpolicy%2Falkire-foster-methodology%2F%5C%22%3EAlkire%20%26amp%3B%20Foster%20methodology%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20the%20NITI%20Aayog%20has%20also%20used%2C%20is%20the%20discretion%20in%20terms%20of%20deciding%20the%20levels%20of%20deprivation%20and%20weightage%20of%20each%20indicator.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20capabilities%20approach%20does%20something%20that%20no%20other%20poverty%20measurement%20approach%20has%20been%20able%20to%20achieve%3A%20the%20conversion%20of%20capability%20into%20well-being.%20Sen%20and%20Nussbaum%20call%20it%20a%20%E2%80%98conversion%20handicap%E2%80%99%2C%20which%20would%20be%20multiplied%20when%20measuring%20poverty%20indicators%20for%20people%20with%20disabilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20aspect%20that%20MPI%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20cater%20to%20is%20the%20need%20to%20understand%20the%20quality%20of%20the%20indicators.%20Due%20to%20the%20lack%20of%20a%20benchmark%20for%20these%20indicators%2C%20the%20assessment%20that%20a%20person%20who%20has%20attended%20school%20for%20ten%20years%20is%20not%20deprived%20is%20at%20the%20very%20least%20faulty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Sustainable%20Development%20Goals%20(SDGs)%20provide%20a%20powerful%20framework%20covering%20access%20to%20education%20and%20employment%2C%20availability%20of%20schools%20that%20are%20sensitive%20to%20students%20with%20disabilities%2C%20inclusion%20and%20empowerment%20of%20persons%20with%20disabilities%2C%20accessible%20transport%2C%20accessible%20public%20and%20green%20spaces%2C%20and%20building%20the%20capacity%20of%20countries%20to%20disaggregate%20data%20by%20disability%2C%20none%20of%20which%20is%20unfortunately%20taken%20into%20consideration%20while%20studying%20poverty%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20SDGs%20seek%20to%20%E2%80%98leave%20no%20one%20behind%E2%80%9D%2C%20NITI%20Aayog%E2%80%99s%20MPI%20is%20regrettably%20leaving%20behind%20people%20with%20disabilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20question%20that%20arises%20now%20is%2C%20how%20the%20MPI%20could%20have%20included%20disability%20in%20its%20study.%20One%20way%20would%20be%20to%20include%20disability%20as%20an%20indicator.%20But%20this%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20necessarily%20fit%2C%20as%20disability%20alone%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20make%20someone%20poor%3B%20it%E2%80%99s%20the%20inaccessibility%20and%20resulting%20inequality%20in%20society%20that%20deprives%20them%20of%20opportunities%2C%20in%20turn%20making%20them%20poor.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20issue%20with%20large-scale%20studies%20is%20that%20the%20collected%20data%20isn%E2%80%99t%20disaggregated%20enough%20to%20be%20made%20available%20for%20intersectional%20studies.%20The%20current%20MPI%20report%20has%20disaggregated%20data%20from%20a%20geographical%20perspective%3B%20however%2C%20including%20a%20disability%20status%20in%20the%20next%20data%20collection%20cycle%20would%20assist%20policymakers%20in%20making%20targeted%20policy%20changes%20to%20address%20poverty%20as%20well%20as%20disability-related%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20could%20also%20work%20is%20a%20participatory%20approach%20to%20selecting%20variables%2C%20which%20would%20include%20people%20with%20disabilities%20in%20the%20consultation%20process%20for%20developing%20poverty%20metrics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20writer%20is%20manager%20at%20Policy%20Advocacy%20and%20Coordination%20at%20the%20Association%20of%20People%20with%20Disabilities.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20originally%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Fopinion%2Fpanorama%2Fwhy-niti-aayog-report-must-include-disability-data-1240737.html%5C%22%3Epublished%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2F%5C%22%3EDeccan%20Herald.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690377328000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F06%2F04145307%2F2865509591_9a0974b029_k.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fwhy-the-niti-aayog-report-must-include-data-on-the-disabled-population%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22NITI%20Aayog%E2%80%99s%20Mutlidimensional%20Poverty%20Index%20is%20regrettably%20leaving%20behind%20people%20with%20disabilities.%20However%2C%20an%20inclusive%20policy%20demands%20that%20disability's%20impact%20on%20poverty%20be%20addressed%20and%20includes%20a%20capabilities%20approach.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fwhy-the-niti-aayog-report-must-include-data-on-the-disabled-population%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22BBC%20reporter%20at%20scene%20of%20Rhodes%20wildfire%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690377261000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F133A%2Fproduction%2F_130522940_p0g2zx0z.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A