ave-of-absence-as-corruption-probe-continues-2019-11-1028653072%5C%22%3Eyearslong%20federal%20investigation%20into%20financial%20corruption.%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20fate%20of%20about%20150%2C000%20union-represented%20workers%20at%20the%20Big%20Three%20hangs%20in%20the%20balance%20as%20the%20two%20sides%20hash%20out%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-layoffs-workers-jobs-careers-hiring-auto-industry-2023-1%5C%22%3Efuture%20of%20work%20in%20an%20increasingly%20electrified%20industry%20%3C%2Fa%3Ethat%20will%20likely%20see%20less%20and%20less%20internal-combustion%20engine%20production%20and%20more%20battery%20production.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20talks%20come%20amid%20the%20backdrop%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funions-having-major-moment-but-dont-expect-1930s-level-boom-2023-7%5C%22%3Ea%20newly%20emboldened%20labor%20movement%20across%20the%20country%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20several%20high-profile%20strikes%20and%20organizing%20pushes%20in%20the%20entertainment%2C%20food%2C%20and%20retail%20industries.%20UAW%20President%20Shawn%20Fain%2C%20who%20was%20elected%20by%20a%20narrow%20margin%20in%20March%2C%20is%20leaning%20into%20this%20labor%20movement%2C%20eschewing%20long-standing%20traditions%20like%20ceremonial%20handshakes%20with%20the%20automotive%20CEOs%20in%20favor%20of%20connecting%20with%20his%20members.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe's%20taken%20to%20Facebook%20Live%20in%20recent%20months%20to%20speak%20directly%20to%20his%20members%2C%20preparing%20them%20for%20a%20potential%20strike.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20to%20be%20able%20to%20do%20whatever%20we%20have%20to%20do%20if%20you%20want%20to%20have%20these%20gains.%20The%20companies%20aren't%20going%20to%20freely%20give%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Fain%20said%20in%20June.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEscalating%20tactics%20at%20the%20UAW%20predate%20Fain.%20In%202019%2C%20at%20the%20height%20of%20the%20union's%20corruption%20scandal%2C%20the%20UAW%20initiated%20a%2040-day%20strike%20at%20GM's%20more%20than%2030%20US%20factories.%20The%20work%20stoppage%20helped%20the%20union%20notch%20wins%20on%20wages%20and%20job%20security%2C%20even%20as%20the%20company%20won%20the%20ability%20to%20close%20several%20factories.%20In%20the%20end%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmedia.gm.com%2Fcontent%2Fdam%2FMedia%2Fgmcom%2Finvestor%2F2019%2Foct%2Fgm-q3-2019-earnings-press-release-1029.pdf%5C%22%3EGM%20lost%20some%20%243.6%20billion%3C%2Fa%3E%20due%20to%20the%20strike.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20union%2C%20which%20also%20covers%20workers%20in%20other%20industrial%20industries%20and%20some%20academic%20institutions%2C%20has%20also%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F10000-john-deere-workers-on-strike-over-failed-contract-negotiations-2021-10%5C%22%3Ehigh-profile%20work%20stoppages%20at%20John%20Deere%20in%202021%20%3C%2Fa%3Eand%20the%20University%20of%20California%20in%202022.%20Fain%20has%20said%20he%20is%20not%20ruling%20out%20a%20strike%20in%20this%20round%20of%20talks%2C%20potentially%20at%20more%20than%20one%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EElectric%20vehicles%20will%20change%20things%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20first%20round%20of%20negotiations%20between%20the%20Detroit%20car%20companies%20and%20the%20UAW%20in%20which%20electric%20vehicles%20will%20be%20front%20and%20center.%20EVs%20were%20an%20undercurrent%20in%20the%202019%20negotiations%2C%20but%20since%20then%20the%20segment%20has%20grown%20exponentially%20and%20companies%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fautomakers-ford-gm-electric-vehicle-prices-battery-cost-rise-2022-12%5C%22%3EFord%20and%20GM%20have%20made%20firm%20commitments%20to%20build%20more%20EVs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20require%20less%20labor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20car%20companies%20will%20be%20looking%20for%20more%20flexibility%20to%20respond%20to%20changes%20in%20demand%20for%20EVs%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fford-electric-vehicle-inventory-problem-trying-to-beat-tesla-2023-7%5C%22%3Ewhich%20is%20already%20creating%20headaches%20for%20companies%20like%20Ford%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20UAW%20will%20be%20looking%20for%20assurances%20that%20their%20work%20will%20be%20protected%20even%20as%20it%20changes%2C%20and%20that%20wages%20will%20continue%20to%20improve%20even%20as%20the%20companies%20look%20to%20remain%20competitive%20with%20EV-makers%20like%20Tesla%20who%20use%20cheaper%20non-union%20labor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20there%20is%20the%20issue%20of%20powertrain%20production.%20At%20GM%2C%20an%20Ultium%20battery%20plant%20has%20taken%20the%20place%20of%20Lordstown%20Assembly%2C%20which%20closed%20after%20the%2040-day%20strike%20in%202019.%20The%20labor%20force%20there%20is%20not%20UAW-represented.%20Ford%20is%20building%20a%20new%20EV%20campus%20in%20Tennessee%2C%20which%20is%20also%20not%20yet%20unionized.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20industry%20moves%20away%20from%20historically%20unionized%20engine%20production%20and%20toward%20new%20battery%20plants%20that%20have%20not%20yet%20been%20unionized%2C%20the%20topic%20of%20job%20security%20will%20be%20at%20the%20forefront%20of%20EV%20talks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ELabor%20costs%20are%20small%2C%20but%20the%20only%20thing%20in%20the%20company's%20control%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cost%20of%20labor%20only%20accounts%20for%20roughly%205%25%20of%20the%20cost%20of%20building%20a%20vehicle%2C%20but%20it's%20the%20only%20part%20of%20vehicle%20production%20costs%20that%20companies%20can%20exert%20control%20over.%20This%20small%20piece%20of%20the%20pie%20is%20going%20to%20be%20even%20more%20important%20for%20companies%20to%20control%20in%20the%20next%20four%20years%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fautomakers-rising-electric-vehicle-battery-costs-lithium-affordability-2022-12%5C%22%3Eas%20commodity%20costs%20become%20more%20difficult%20to%20predict%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20average%20labor%20costs%20for%20the%20Detroit%20Three%20heading%20into%20contract%20talks%20four%20years%20ago%20hovered%20between%20%2455%20and%20%2460%20per%20hour.%20After%20the%20agreements%20in%202019%2C%20the%20Center%20for%20Automotive%20Research%20forecasted%20labor%20cost%20increases%20between%2013%25%20and%2020%25.%20That%20average%20includes%20wages%20and%20benefits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20it's%20unlikely%20that%20the%20companies%20will%20be%20able%20to%20bring%20these%20costs%20down%2C%20they%20will%20be%20looking%20for%20ways%20to%20keep%20them%20from%20going%20up%20too%20much.%20However%2C%20some%20estimates%20based%20on%20what%20the%20UAW%20has%20won%20outside%20the%20automotive%20industry%20in%20the%20last%20four%20years%20put%20potential%20increases%20in%20labor%20costs%20between%2025%25%20and%2030%25%20over%20the%20next%20four%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENegotiations%20formally%20began%20at%20all%20three%20companies%20last%20week.%20The%20current%20contracts%20are%20set%20to%20expire%20September%2014.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuaw-auto-workers-union-negotiations-contract-strike-ford-gm-stellantis-2023-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690377223000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64c0072aed4f4600196358a3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuaw-auto-workers-union-negotiations-contract-strike-ford-gm-stellantis-2023-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Ford%2C%20GM%2C%20and%20Stellantis%20have%20returned%20to%20the%20bargaining%20table%20to%20hash%20out%20a%20four-year%20deal%20with%20the%20United%20Auto%20Workers%20and%20avoid%20a%20possible%20strike.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22nnaughton%40insider.com%20(Nora%20Naughton)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuaw-auto-workers-union-negotiations-contract-strike-ford-gm-stellantis-2023-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%